title: 2010.06.12-F1.08.Canada.Qualifying.BBC2_UK [TDMK1]
description:
2010.06.12-F1.08.Canada.Qualifying.BBC2_UK-TDMK1.m4v

Jake Humphrey is joined by Eddie Jordan and David Coulthard for live coverage of today's session at the Circuit Gilles-Villeneuve in Montreal, as the drivers contest grid positions for the eighth race of the season. This round returns to the calendar after a two-year absence. Lewis Hamilton qualified on pole when it was last held, but lasted only 19 laps during the race following a pit-lane collision with Kimi Raikkonen, as Robert Kubica went on to take victory. Commentary by Jonathan Legard and Martin Brundle.

Now encoded as 'MP4 All Play'... As a departure from the DivX files which I have uploaded in the past, I've made the decision to get with the 21st century & start encoding with the following specs this year;

MP4 - 640x352 - 800Kb/s H264 Video - 44.1KHz/128Kbps Stereo AAC Audio

My belief is this is the best all round setup, and hopefully you will agree!

This video will play on a computer with VLC, XBMC, XBox360, PS3, iPad all iPhones - enjoy the show... :)
